educationLevel: This plant is 3 feet tall and has several long narrow and bendable branches that are a reddish-brown
format: color. It is growing out of a sawed-off tree. The buds are growing out of the stems and the tips of the branches. The buds have a
hasPart: petal that builds into the flower. The scales are coral-yellow-red. The budding leaves are light green. Possibly, it's the original tree growing, or it's an epiphyte since it's growing out of a multi-tree stump. I also found another tree located along the bluff-it's shown the the other two pictures.

hasPart: . I found it strange that the ground around the tree was littered with big older leaves. Did they come from a bigger Bigleaf Maple the I failed to notice (and then if so, then how come its leaves grew and fell before the smaller tree)? If not, then how come the old leaves hadn't decayed more before the tree started growing new leaves? How long ago did those leaves fall?
